<%
  set_seo_meta(
    title: "Acceptable Use Policy - BizBlasts",
    description: "Acceptable Use Policy for BizBlasts: what businesses, staff, and customers can and cannot do on the BizBlasts platform and on sites we host.",
    canonical: "https://www.bizblasts.com/acceptableusepolicy"
  )

  effective_date = "June 1, 2026"
  support_email  = ENV.fetch('SUPPORT_EMAIL', 'bizblaststeam@gmail.com')
%>

<%= render layout: 'shared/legal_page',
           locals: {
             eyebrow: 'Acceptable Use Policy',
             title: 'Acceptable Use Policy',
             summary: "Conduct, content, and security rules that apply to everyone using the BizBlasts platform and sites we host, including business owners, staff, and end customers.",
             effective_date: effective_date,
             contact_email: support_email
           } do %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '1. Scope' } do %>
    <p>
      This Acceptable Use Policy (&ldquo;AUP&rdquo;) applies to all use of the BizBlasts platform, including
      our website, the application, custom-domain sites we host, communications features (SMS, email, calls),
      payment processing, and APIs. It supplements our
      <%= link_to 'Terms of Service', '/terms', class: 'text-primary hover:underline' %>
      and applies to business owners, staff, end customers, and anyone else who interacts with the platform.
    </p>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '2. Lawful Use' } do %>
    <p>
      You must use BizBlasts only for lawful purposes and in compliance with all applicable laws and
      regulations, including consumer-protection, privacy, marketing, telecom, tax, sector-specific, and
      licensing rules that apply to your business.
    </p>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '3. Prohibited Content and Activities' } do %>
    <p>You may not use BizBlasts to publish, transmit, store, or facilitate any of the following:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
      <li>Content that is illegal, infringes intellectual-property rights, or violates rights of privacy or publicity.</li>
      <li>Sexually explicit content involving minors, child sexual abuse material, or any other content that exploits or endangers children.</li>
      <li>Threats of violence, harassment, stalking, hateful conduct, or content that incites violence against an individual or group.</li>
      <li>Fraudulent, deceptive, or misleading offers, claims, reviews, testimonials, pricing, or business credentials.</li>
      <li>Unsolicited bulk email, unsolicited SMS, robocalls, scraping, phishing, malware distribution, or other abusive communications.</li>
      <li>Sales of goods or services prohibited by law where they are sold, or sales prohibited by our payment processor (for example, items on Stripe&rsquo;s restricted list).</li>
      <li>Multi-level-marketing schemes, pyramid schemes, gambling, drug paraphernalia, weapons, or other categories restricted by the payment processor.</li>
      <li>Content that misrepresents your identity, your business, or your affiliation with a person or organization.</li>
    </ul>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '4. Platform Integrity and Security' } do %>
    <p>You may not, and must not allow others to:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
      <li>Probe, scan, or test the vulnerability of any BizBlasts system without our prior written consent.</li>
      <li>Bypass or attempt to bypass authentication, authorization, rate limits, multi-tenant isolation, billing, or any other access controls.</li>
      <li>Interfere with the proper functioning of the platform, including by overloading systems, abusing background workers, or sending excessive automated requests.</li>
      <li>Reverse engineer, decompile, or attempt to extract the source code of the platform, except as expressly permitted by law.</li>
      <li>Access data belonging to other tenants, other users, or other businesses without authorization.</li>
      <li>Use the platform to build, train, or benchmark a competing product, except to the extent prohibited by law.</li>
    </ul>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '5. Communications: Email, SMS, and Calls' } do %>
    <p>
      If you use email, SMS, or calling features, you are responsible for collecting valid consent from your
      recipients and honoring opt-out, unsubscribe, and do-not-call requests. You must:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
      <li>Only send messages to recipients who have agreed to receive them.</li>
      <li>Include accurate sender identification and, where required, a clear way to opt out.</li>
      <li>Honor opt-outs (such as <code class="rounded bg-gray-100 px-1 py-0.5 text-[0.95em] text-dark">STOP</code>) promptly across all related lists.</li>
      <li>Avoid using BizBlasts for high-risk message types (premium SMS, lotteries, certain regulated industries) that are prohibited by our carriers or the law.</li>
    </ul>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '6. Customer Data' } do %>
    <p>
      If you collect, process, or store data about customers, leads, or other end users through your
      BizBlasts site, you are responsible for handling that data lawfully, securely, and in line with the
      promises you make to those individuals. Do not upload data you do not have the right to use, and do not
      use BizBlasts to handle data categories the platform is not designed for.
    </p>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '7. Reporting Abuse' } do %>
    <p>
      To report content or behavior that violates this AUP &mdash; for example, a BizBlasts-hosted site that
      appears to be fraudulent, infringing, or unsafe &mdash; please email
      <%= mail_to support_email, support_email, class: "text-primary hover:underline" %>
      with as much detail as possible (URL, date and time, and a description of the issue).
    </p>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '8. Enforcement' } do %>
    <p>
      We investigate suspected violations of this AUP and may take action that we consider appropriate, up to
      and including removing content, suspending or terminating accounts, removing custom domains, refusing
      service, retaining or refunding fees, and cooperating with law-enforcement requests. We may act without
      prior notice when the situation warrants (for example, to protect users, third parties, or the
      platform).
    </p>
  <% end %>

  <%= render layout: 'shared/legal_section', locals: { title: '9. Changes' } do %>
    <p>
      We may update this AUP from time to time. If we make material changes, we may post the revised version
      on the site, update the effective date above, or use other reasonable means to notify you.
    </p>
  <% end %>

<% end %>
